title: For Sale/Trade:  1904 Sparkbrook Lee Enfield mk1***
postcontent: I have an early (first year of production) 1904 Lee Enfield mk1*** made at Sparkbrook. This rifle went through British use in WWI and was then given to Ireland after the war of independence and marked with the ER serial prefix indicating Irish use. The rifle was then overhauled for grenade firing for Irish use and given a G serial prefix. Ireland used rifle grenades extensively as they did not have an adequate amount of mortars. Few G series rifles were produced and this is an early rifle with lots of history. The bore is good. Still has the early charger guide on the bolt head along with the volley sight. Looking to trade for a WW1 Lee Enfield with cutoff, FF marked Lee Enfield, Lee Enfield no1 mkIII, or a nice Finn m39 with some cash or ammo. Thank you.

title: For Sale:  1904 Sparkbrook Lee Enfield mk1***
postcontent: I have an early (first year of production) 1904 Lee Enfield mk1*** made at Sparkbrook. This rifle went through British use in WWI and was then given to Ireland after the war of independence and marked with the ER serial prefix indicating Irish use. The rifle was then overhauled for grenade firing for Irish use and given a G serial prefix. Ireland used rifle grenades extensively as they did not have an adequate amount of mortars. Few G series rifles were produced and this is an early rifle with lots of history. The bore is good. Still has the early charger guide on the bolt head along with the volley sight. Looking to trade for a WW1 Lee Enfield with cutoff, FF marked Lee Enfield, Lee Enfield no1 mkIII, or a nice Finn m39 with some cash or ammo. Thank you.
